        [
          "Native American, roams SoCal, does recon on Sabbat and others.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Jenn Wolfe"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Your people lived in this region for thousands of years, but you weren't born till their culture was already well on the decline. You learned the old ways, of Quaoar who gave the law to your people. Your path was that of a spiritual leader rather than political, but that all changed when the friars and padres arrived. They brought with them their crucified god and had no use for the spirits you saw or the laws your people followed. You remember as they establish the Mission de San Gabriel Arcangel and you vowed you wouln't become enslaved to this foreign god like everyone else. You ran for the desert, hiding from the missionaries, watching in the darkness. In the darkness someone found you. Your sire liked the missionaries no better than you, and the pair of you took to wandering, avoiding the growing influence of Westerners until you realized you couldn't anymore. Your sire left, seeking a place free of the growing influence of vampiric society, but you stayed and more or less found yourself in the Camarilla. You weren't sold on it, but it served its purpose, and you skirted the edges out of necessity. Besides, it wasn't the Sabbat, whose religious fervor reminded you too much of the very missionaries you fled from when you were young, and you were more than happy to roam the deserts, watching for their incursions, like a pestilence. When the Camarilla fell and the Tara's barony rose you didn't pay that much attention. After all, you were hunting Sabbat, and the Anarchs loved them no better, so your services were still useful. Through the changes from Camarilla, to Anarch, to Camarilla again, you've stayed constant, caring little who is in charge as long as they can hold the line against the religious zealots to the south. You've been out in the desert and have missed out on recent events. You've heard John David Hopkins is the new prince and he's making a mess of it. There's always been someone in San Diego holding the line, but should he fall there's no one. You've come out of the desert to offer your skills to make sure that the Sabbat don't take advantage of the situation and scream across the border."
        ],
        [
